        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 1:00AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 100 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
northwest of Beaver, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Pleasant Ridge...                 Urbanette...
Berryville...                     Beaver...
Grandview...                      Oak Hill...
Busch...                          Eureka Springs...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
